1.23
log
@Don't completely scare off people by saying that enabling ACPI will
cause their hardware to spontaneously selfcombust.  Instead, mention
that using acpitz(4) should prevent this from happening.

(I tested it one night by accident when I fell asleep with my laptop
on the couch and blocked the fan with a blanket.)

ok jmc marco
@
text
@d1 1
a1 1
.\"	$OpenBSD: acpi.4,v 1.22 2007/05/31 19:19:48 jmc Exp $
d17 1
a17 1
.Dd $Mdocdate: May 31 2007 $
a26 1
.Cd "option ACPI_ENABLE"
a37 12
.Pp
If the configuration option
.Dq Dv ACPI_ENABLE
is set, the
.Nm
driver will take control of ACPI from the firmware (BIOS).
WARNING: this may cause an overheating on some machines since
.Nm
doesn't provide any thermal or cooling control.
For thermal control, use
.Xr acpitz 4
to shut down the system when temperatures exceed critical limits.
@


